00:41:52,196 --> 00:41:55,314
(speaking Polish)

941
00:41:58,819 --> 00:42:00,619
All right, get up.
Put your hands behind your back.

942
00:42:00,621 --> 00:42:02,788
♪ Everything

943
00:42:02,790 --> 00:42:06,242
♪ Is crystal clear...

944
00:42:06,244 --> 00:42:07,376
I did it!

945
00:42:07,378 --> 00:42:08,861
Close that door immediately!

946
00:42:08,863 --> 00:42:11,029
What's up?

947
00:42:11,031 --> 00:42:12,581
I was examining
the osmia avoseta

948
00:42:12,583 --> 00:42:14,700
that Gerald Lydon gave me,
and it got loose.

949
00:42:14,702 --> 00:42:17,803
Oh, so there's an almost-extinct
bee flying around in here?

950
00:42:17,805 --> 00:42:19,805
Yes, and I would rather
it didn't get out.

951
00:42:19,807 --> 00:42:21,423
Okay. Well, I
took care of it.

952
00:42:21,425 --> 00:42:23,058
That dry cleaner
you sent me to,

953
00:42:23,060 --> 00:42:24,977
you deduced what
they were up to.

954
00:42:24,979 --> 00:42:27,563
Bell sent in somebody to search
it, and everybody's arrested.

955
00:42:27,565 --> 00:42:29,849
Thought I was gonna
have to send you back there

956
00:42:29,851 --> 00:42:31,734
three times more times.
Well done.

957
00:42:31,736 --> 00:42:33,486
Why didn't you tell me
when I came to you yesterday?

958
00:42:33,488 --> 00:42:35,187
I wanted you to...

959
00:42:35,189 --> 00:42:37,106
learn to trust
your own instincts.

